<DocsPageTitle Path="Extensions/PDF" AddedVersion="New">
    Blazorise PDF
</DocsPageTitle>

<DocsPageLead>
    Build PDF document definitions from Razor components or from C# builder code, then generate a PDF file through the PDF generator service.
</DocsPageLead>

<DocsPageSubtitle>
    Installation
</DocsPageSubtitle>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    Install the <Code>Blazorise.Pdf</Code> package and register the PDF generator services in your application startup.
</DocsPageParagraph>

<DocsPageSection>
    <DocsPageSectionHeader Title="NuGet">
        Install extension from NuGet.
    </DocsPageSectionHeader>
    <DocsPageSectionSource Code="PdfNugetInstallExample" />
</DocsPageSection>

<DocsPageSection>
    <DocsPageSectionHeader Title="Imports">
        In your main <Badge Color="Color.Light">_Imports.razor</Badge> add:
    </DocsPageSectionHeader>
    <DocsPageSectionSource Code="PdfImportsExample" />
</DocsPageSection>

<DocsPageSection>
    <DocsPageSectionHeader Title="Services">
        Register the PDF generator once with your Blazorise services.
    </DocsPageSectionHeader>
    <DocsPageSectionSource Code="PdfServiceRegistrationExample" />
</DocsPageSection>

